Saved!
Job Details
To be the initial contact person for clients, staff, and all visitors contacting EMC. To provide professional, courteous, and effective service.Taking messagesFaxing/Scanning /Photocopying/courier as and when required. Document management for internal and external documents. Greeting visitors, answering questions and directing them to the appropriate individuals.Dealing with all incoming calls and transferring calls to the appropriate individuals, Typing a variety of forms, letters, reports and memos. Organizing and maintaining office files and records. Receiving and distributing mails.Assisting in the closing and securing of the office at the end of the work day. Marking attendance on a daily basis and proving an attendance report to HR & Admin Exec bi-monthly
Requirements
Should possess a High School and College Diploma degree 5 years work experience in similar role,  management levelDetail oriented. Highly skilled in organization and prioritizing.Basic Office administration skills Basic knowledge of computer keyboarding and filing is required, as well as strong interpersonal communication skills and effective decision-making capability.
